SIMPLE: overdrive
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Overdrive
<hw>O`ver*drive"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t. & i.</pos> <def>To drive
too hard, or far, or beyond strength.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>overdrive</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: overdrive
<hw>o"ver*drive`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Machinery)</fld> <def>A gearing device which causes the drive
shaft of an automobile or other machine to rotate at a speed greater
than that of the engine crankshaft.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Automotive)</fld> <def>The gear setting of a motor
vehicle at which the overdrive{1} is operative; <as>as, cruising at 80
mph in <ex>overdrive</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <specif>Hence:</specif> <mark>[fig.]</mark> <def>A state
of unusually intense activity; <as>as, when they got their new
supercomputer, their research kicked into <ex>overdrive</ex>; one look
at her made his heart jump into <ex>overdrive</ex></as>; -- used mostly
of the activities of persons or groups.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Overdrown</ent>⟦br⟧
